# Lodash

## Import style

```typescript
import _trim from "lodash/trim";
import _isEmpty from "lodash/isEmpty";
```

- One import per function from **`lodash/<name>`**; prefix binding with **`_`**
- Do not use **`import _ from "lodash"`** or **`import * as _ from "lodash"`**

## Prefer lodash by default

Use lodash for collection, object, string, and predicate helpers when a lodash function exists — it guards **`null`** / **`undefined`**.

| Prefer lodash | Use native when |
| --- | --- |
| `_map`, `_filter`, `_find`, `_sortBy`, `_keys`, `_trim`, `_isEmpty`, … | `for…of` with **`break`**, **`?.` / `??`** on one known path, template literals |

- Prefer **`_sortBy`** / **`_orderBy`** over **`[...arr].sort(compareFn)`** unless in-place sort is intentional
- In **`src/utils`** and **factories**, default to lodash on unknown-shaped values

## Performance

- Do not use **`isEqual`**, deep **`merge`**, or similar in hot paths (SSE, per-request catalog/meta) unless measured
- Prefer shallow checks, ids, or minimal hashes for diffs
